author: Bruce Arthur
title: NFL pick: Ground is shaking under Seahawks
text:
Seattle (-6.5) at San Francisco
In the fourth quarter of Seattle’s six games, opposing quarterbacks — Nick Foles, Aaron Rodgers, Jimmy Clausen, Matt Stafford, Andy Dalton and Cam Newton — are 52-for-63 for 611 yards, four touchdowns, and no interceptions. The Seahawks have only beaten Chicago with Jimmy Clausen throwing footballs the way an average person throws a desk, and the Lions, who were the last team to win a game in the NFL this year. And they beat the Lions by a field goal. Everyone talks about the San Francisco collapse, but the ground is close to giving way beneath the Seahawks, too.
Pick: San Francisco
